Contributing to Capital One's iOS app adding new features and feature refinement in Swift.
Developed and debugged Sephora in-store sales apps (Swift and Objective-C).

Solo architect, designer and developer of the StylSavvy platform software consisting of an iOS app and backend server/database.  StylSavvy is a fashion shopping/styling iOS app with a database of over 260,000 products from leading retailers ranging from Macy’s to Saks.  I originally developed and marketed the software platform between 2011-2013 and completely redesigned it this year.  It's turned into my hobby app that I use to keep up with new iOS features and marketing concepts.The Objective C iOS app supports iOS 8 and iOS 9 features including Class Sizes and Auto-Layouts to universally support the iPhone and iPad in all orientations. Animations, custom Presentation Controllers, Core Data, NSOperations, GCD, image manipulation, smooth infinite scrolling. CocoaPods: Facebook, AFNetorking, SDWebImage.Heroku RoR server provides a JSON API to the app. Implemented Memcache to reduce HTTP request/response times. Used Twitter Bootstrap to design the landing page.  Mongo database of product data uses compound indexing to minimize access latency.  Run Ruby scripts on FTP downloaded merchandiser files to generate the product database.

Restructured an existing iOS app, reducing its size from 150 Mbytes to 51 Mbytes.  Created a universal app using adaptive layout and size classes.  Replaced the ‘Hamburger’ navigation with the Tab Bar Navigation.  Architected, designed and coded new product features. Implemented HTTP Live Streaming color instruction videos.  Defined and developed a new Color Matching feature.Worked closely with the Design team to refine new designs to conform to Apple’s Human Interface Guidelines resulting in faster software development and cleaner code.

Contributed to the development of a universal iPhone/iPad app that converts 2D pictures of buildings to 3D images.  Designed and developed an m-commerce feature, the map location based search, and the app’s log-in.  Debugged Core Data threading issues. Identified UIWebView JavaScript bridge timing issues.
